# docker-compose builds both services from the repo ROOT context (the
# Dockerfiles use Railway-style root-relative COPY paths: `COPY backend/…`,
# `COPY frontend/…`). Docker only honours the .dockerignore at the context
# root, so the per-directory backend/.dockerignore and frontend/.dockerignore
# are NOT applied under this context — this file unions them.
#
# The critical one is frontend/node_modules: without it, `COPY frontend/ .`
# copies the host's (darwin/arm64) node_modules over the image's `npm ci`
# result, and the platform-specific esbuild/rollup binaries break `npm run
# build`. The rest avoid baking secrets / caches / build output into images.
.git
**/.env
**/*.log
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
**/*.egg-info
backend/.venv
backend/.pytest_cache
backend/.mypy_cache
frontend/node_modules
frontend/dist
